2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 206
BY REPRESENTATIVE DICKERSON
A RESOLUTION
To authorize and direct the Department of Transportation and Development to complete the
Louisiana Highway 16 widening project from Louisiana Highway 1019 to Louisiana
Highway 1023.
WHEREAS, approximately twenty-five thousand drivers use Louisiana Highway 16
(LA-16) daily; and
WHEREAS, there a numerous businesses on Louisiana Highway 1019 (LA-1019),
LA-16, and Louisiana Highway 1023 (LA-1023), including but not limited to the Oak Point
Fresh Market, Livingston Parish Fire Protection District #4 Station, restaurants, and clothing
stores; and
WHEREAS, LA-1019 to LA-1023 is only a two-lane road; and
WHEREAS, according to the World Population Review, Livingston Parish's
population has increased five and one half percent since 2020; and
WHEREAS, according to the office of operations, within the Federal Highway
Administration, lack of physical capacity contributes to congestion, thus, widening highways
is an important strategy and is critical for alleviating congestion; and
WHEREAS, widening highways improves commuter satisfaction by reducing
congestion and decreasing driving times; and
WHEREAS, there is already capital outlay funding from the 2024 Regular Session
dedicated to widening LA-16, but the project has yet to begin.
